The paper presents a mathematical model for characterizing the meaning of words, which suggests a natural fit with the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of Markov processes and statistical operations also suggests a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper's focus on extracting topics and discovering synonyms suggests a connection to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on language-independent semantic representations suggests a connection to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
